Title: Congratulation made to the betrothed couple at Amsterdam.
Description.note: Congratulation made to the betrothed couple at Amsterdam.A.  The betrothed couple, before a looking glass.  B. The woman’s mother and relations.  C. The man’s mother and relations.  D. Paranimphs, who go to meet the ladys and present them to the betrothed couple.  E. Those who after having done their compliments place the [?] in both sides of the room.  F. Apartment where the men go to congratulate the relations after having complemented the betrothed couple.  G. Sweet meats presented [?] and then to the ladies.  H. A man in the ceremony who serves up the sweet meats wine & [?].  Ceremony called by the Dutch Palmknoopen which consists in tying and [?] flowers together and some leaves of Trainasse which they throw at the married couple.  Some young people of both sexes invited to the ceremony set them two days before the wedding day They put also golden and silver leaves and stick some upon the leaves of the Trainasse.

Marriage ceremony of the Protestants at Amsterdam.  A. The married couple.  B. The Paranimphs & friends.  C. The minister.  D. The deacon with the purse to receive the alms of the married couple.
